Heat oven to 300 degrees F. Combine cookie crumbs and butter; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch springform pan. In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add eggs, chocolate, dissolved coffee and vanilla. Mix well. Stir in 3/4 cup chips. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Chill. Just before serving, remove side of springform pan. Garnish with whipped topping and remaining 1/4 cup chips. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.